		<description>The downsides of regular ashlands with none of the benefits. A bleak wasteland littered with the corpses of dead silt striders. The sky is almost permanently covered in a thick cloud of ash. Any rain that falls here contains ash-blight, driving animals mad and causing crop blights. Few animals and plants are capable of living here, with the waters being completely devoid of life. Unless you enjoy eating scathecraw, food will be difficult to obtain. There have also been sightings of corprus victims wandering aimlessly. Only fools settle here.</description>
